    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a US military posture characterized by sustained forward-deployed operations and heightened readiness across multiple domains. Two aircraft carriers, USS Gerald R. Ford and USS Nimitz, are actively deployed in critical theaters—the Ford in the Middle East (Strait of Hormuz) and the Nimitz in the Pacific (Southern Seas 2026 exercises)—demonstrating a dual-carrier strategy to deter adversarial actions while supporting allied engagements. Strategic airlift operations remain robust, with multiple C-17 and C-5M sorties indicating sustained logistical support for global operations, including urgent deployment requirements and European theater support. ISR and AEW&amp;C platforms, including a Beechcraft King Air 200 and a Boeing E-35L, underscore a continued emphasis on regional monitoring, particularly in the Indo-Pacific and Middle East. The presence of high-altitude unidentified aircraft suggests potential electronic warfare or advanced ISR activities. Notably, the recent commissioning of USS Harvey C. Barnum Jr. (DDG-124) reflects ongoing naval modernization, though its in-port status indicates a transitional phase. Joint training activities, including Australian PC-21 and USMC V-22 Osprey operations, highlight interoperability efforts with allied forces. The overall assessment indicates a deliberate strategy to maintain persistent power projection, deter aggression, and support allied operations amid evolving regional threats, particularly in the Middle East and Indo-Pacific.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
